An industrialist and Chief Executive Officer of Wellmann Group of Companies, Deacon Chris Iyovwaye, has joined  the Delta State governorship race. Iyovwaye, who hails from Aghalokpe in Okpe Local Government in Delta Central Senatorial District, said he is vying for the position on the platform of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP).   ‘Make technology centre of agricultural…     Agency chief declares for Reps     ‘Ojo APC should be repositioned for success’   Iyovwaye  told his supporters: “I have formed a strong affiliation with different political interests across the state.  I believe the state is one of the most endowed in the country and has the capacity of becoming an industrial and commercial hub, with the right leadership. “I am passionate about alleviating the hardship that is endemic among our people. It’s all about the yearning by the people for respect, humility, and true leadership as against rulership. “As a visionary leader, I am determined to restore the dignity of the average Delta indigene, if elected as the next governor.”